m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҶҗ" "
  LEFT ARROW вҶҗ

  Keyboard: `[

  Assign: bind a variable name to a value

  Examples:

  v вҶҗ 1 2 3 4
  (i (j k)) вҶҗ (10 (11 12))
  v +вҶҗ 1
  f вҶҗ О»-
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҮҗ" "
  LEFT FAT ARROW вҮҗ

  Keyboard: `U    

  Assign to function: bind a variable name to a function
 
  Note that lambda functions are assigned with вҶҗ and not вҮҗ

  Examples:
    
  f вҮҗ +вҢҝ
  f вҮҗ { (вҚө+вҚә)Г·2 }
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҹҰ" "
  LEFT FAT BRACKET вҹҰ

  Keyboard: `5

  Function argument list open: When you call a function, you use fat brackets to input function arguments. 
  The given list is treated as having a length of 1, as opposed to calling a function with N-tuple, which
  has length N.
  
  Example:

  io2:openвҹҰ\"/foo\" ; :inputвҹ§
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҹ§" "
  RIGHT FAT BRACKET вҹ§

  Keyboard: `6

  Function argument list close: When you call a function, you use fat brackets to input function arguments. 
  The given list is treated as having a length of 1, as opposed to calling a function with N-tuple, which
  has length N.

  Example:

  вҲҮ foo (a;b;c) { a+b+c } вӢ„ foo вҹҰ1;2;foo вҹҰ10;11;12вҹ§вҹ§
"
