  STILE |

  Monadic function:  Magnitude (Absolute value) 
 
  | 2.3 ВҜ4 0 3j4 
в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ2.3 4 0 5.0в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
 
  Dyadic function: Residue (Remainder/Modulus)
  The Residue function, denoted by |, computes the remainder of a division. In the 
  expression R вҶҗ X|Y, R is the remainder when Y is divided by X (note that the 
  arguments are reversed compared to the division expression YГ·X).
 
  2 10 ВҜ2.5 | 7 ВҜ13 8 
