  Dyadic function: Reshape, AвҚҙB reshapes B into the dimensions specified by A. The resulting array with have 
  Г—/A elements. If the total number of elements in A is less than that of B, the extra elements will be dropped. 
  If the total number of elements in A is greater than that of B, the values will wrap around to fill the result 
  array. If B is scalar, every element of the resulting array will have this value.

  2 3 4 вҚҙ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 
