  BECAUSE вҲө

  Keyboard: `S

  Monadic operator: Derive Bitwise, derives a version of the underlying function which performs its operation 
  on the individual bits of an integer. The following bitwise operations are implemented:
  +: xor   -: xor    вү : xor    =: xnor    Г—: and    вҲ§: and    вҲЁ: or    вҚІ: nand    вҚұ: nor
  вүӨ: bitwise less than or equal           <: bitwise less than
  вүҘ: bitwise greater than or equal        >: bitwise greater than
  вҚҙ: number of bits required to store the integer value, excluding any sign bit
  вҚё: count bits      ~: not    вҢҪ: logical shift

  5 +вҲө 3             5 =вҲө 3               5 >вҲө 3               
6                  -7                   4  
  5 вҢҪвҲө 3             5 вҚІвҲө 3               5 -вҲө 3
96                 -2                   6  
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҲҘ" " 
  PARALLEL TO вҲҘ  

  Keyboard: `M

  Monadic operator: Parallel, derives a new function that performs a parallel version of the function it is 
  applied to. The exact behaviour of the derived function depends on the specific underlying function.
  Currently, this operator can only be applied to ВЁ (each). In this case, the result is computed split into 
  separate tasks that are executed in parallel. The number of tasks run in parallel is equal to the number of 
  CPU cores on the system.

  fooВЁ  1 2 3    вҚқ Evaluate foo on each value one by one
  fooВЁвҲҘ 1 2 3    вҚқ Evaluate foo for all the values in parallel
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "О»" " 
  LAMBDA О»

  Keyboard: `V

  Monadic operator: Create Function Reference, О»F creates an anonymous function where F is any function 
  as it appears in an expression. The return value is a primitive value which behaves just like any primitive. 
  It can be passed to other functions, and be members of arrays. When creating a function reference, the function
  captures any lexical bindings references from within the function. These bindings remain valid even after the 
  scope is exited. To call a function from a function reference, use the apply symbol: вҚһ. 

  m1 вҶҗ О»-                     вҚқ monadic projection     
  m2 вҶҗ О»(0-)                  вҚқ monadic projection
  m3 вҶҗ О»{-вҚө}                  вҚқ explicit monad
  arrayOfMonads вҶҗ m1 m2 m3    вҚқ monads                       
  4 {вҚһвҚө вҚә}ВЁ arrayOfMonads
в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ-4 -4 -4в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
"
m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҚһ" " 
  QUOTE QUAD вҚһ

  Keyboard: `{

  Monadic operator: Apply, call a function given its function reference. It can take any of the following forms:
  вҚһvariable calls the function reference stored in variable variable.
  вҚһ(expression) expresion is evaluated to return a function reference which is subsequently called.

  foo вҶҗ О»{1+вҚө}            { вҚһвҚө/ 10 11 12 13 }ВЁ О»Г— О»+   вҚқ (10Г—11Г—12Г—13, 10+11+12+13)
  bar вҶҗ О»{вҚө}            в”ҢвҶ’в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
  вҚһ(вҚһbar foo) 7         в”Ӯ17160 46в”Ӯ
8                       в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
"
