m вҶҗ m mapPut "вҲҮ" " 
  DEL вҲҮ

  Keyboard: `g

  Syntax: Define a global function or operator. 

  The general form is:

  вҲҮ header {
    body
  }
  
  The last evaluated form in body is returned from the function.
  
  The header has the following possible forms:
  
      name вҖ” Declare a function named name. In body, the left argument is accessed using вҚә and the 
      right argument using вҚө.
  
      name x вҖ” The right argument is accessed using the name x. The left argument is not accessible.
  
      x name y вҖ” The left argument is accessed using the name x, and the right argument has the name y.
  
      (a;b) name (d;e) вҖ” The left and right arguments are assumed to be n-tuples and are destructured 
      prior to evaluating the body.
  
      (a name) x вҖ” Monadic operator deriving a monadic function.
  
      x (a name b) y вҖ” Dyadic operator deriving a dyadic function.
  
  When declaring an operator, the function arguments are passed as function objects, and needs to be 
  applied using the function application operation: вҚһ.
  
  To declare a monadic function that returns the argument + 1:
  
  вҲҮ foo x {
    x+1
  }
  
  To declare an operator that adds 100 to the result of evaluating the function after adding 1 to the argument:
  
  вҲҮ (a foo) x {
    result вҶҗ вҚһa 1+x
    100 + result
  }
"
